 a divided civilisation to scrutiny\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Doris_Lessing#cite_note-1\"><span>[<\/span>1<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup> Lessing was the eleventh woman and the oldest person ever to receive the Nobel Prize in Literature.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Doris_Lessing#cite_note-2\"><span>[<\/span>2<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Doris_Lessing#cite_note-3\"><span>[<\/span>3<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-oldest_4-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Doris_Lessing#cite_note-oldest-4\"><span>[<\/span>4<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p><p>In 2001, Lessing was awarded the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/David_Cohen_Prize\" title=\"David Cohen Prize\">David Cohen Prize<\/a> for a lifetime's achievement in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/British_literature\" title=\"British literature\">British literature<\/a>. In 2008, <i><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/The_Times\" title=\"The Times\">The Times<\/a><\/i> ranked her fifth on a list of \"The 50 greatest British writers since 1945\".<sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Doris_Lessing#cite_note-5\"><span>[<\/span>5<span>]<\/span><\/a><\/sup><\/p>","name":"Doris Lessing","place_of_birth":"Kermanshah ,  Iran","place_of_death":"London, United Kingdom","text":"Doris Lessing ,  born in Iran , Literature, 2007","year":2007.0}